# Template-sync allowlist — the only paths the template-sync workflow pulls
# from a new upstream release. One repo-root-relative path per line; blank lines
# and lines starting with `#` are ignored. See .github/workflows/template-sync.yml.
#
# Everything NOT listed here is instance-owned and never touched by the sync:
# your records (registry.csv, print_log.csv), your working schema doc
# (docs/SCHEMA.md), README.md, CHANGELOG.md, CLAUDE.md, and your repointed
# .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml.

# --- Contract mirror -------------------------------------------------------
# Pristine, machine-managed copies of the upstream contract. NEVER hand-edit
# these in an instance — the sync overwrites them wholesale, and their diff is
# the signal you review (a change to template/SCHEMA.md is potentially breaking;
# adopt it into your own docs/SCHEMA.md + registry.csv on your own terms).
template/SCHEMA.md
template/registry.csv
template/print_log.csv
template/README.md
template/CHANGELOG.md

# --- Functional machinery --------------------------------------------------
# GitHub reads these from fixed paths, so they must live (and sync) in place.
# Instances are not expected to customise them (config.yml is the exception and
# is intentionally absent below).
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug.yml
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/chore.yml
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature.yml
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/record.yml
.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/registry-update.md
.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/schema-change.md
.github/pull_request_template.md
.github/workflows/template-sync.yml
.github/.template-sync-paths
